						<summary>

						<p>Door-post of the southern entrance into the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Vikrama-chōḷadēva: Year 20 = 1292-93 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift of two door-posts and two steps to the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> (of the temple) caused to be made and erected, by two women of Śōḻamādēvinallūr, one named Paṟaiyan Āḻuḍaināchchi, a <hi rend="italic">Pūsakar</hi> and her younger mother. </p>						

